			<ns0:name>jvo...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/102292187274959663599/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">&lt;b&gt;- Where are we today?&lt;/b&gt;

We currently borrow some of the application's per-origin HTML5 file system to cache translated PNaCl bitcode (the nexes that come out of that).

This may use some of the application's quota, reserves some random filenames under /.pnacl, and makes the files visible to user code.


&lt;b&gt;- Why is this a problem?&lt;/b&gt;

The files are still copied out and validated before running, but it would be cleaner if it was not visible to the app in this way.



&lt;b&gt;- The proposed enhancement:&lt;/b&gt;

Find a different place to cache pnacl's translated artifacts.


